title: Remnants of Nicole Expected to Take Final Soggy Steps Through Northeast
description: Forecasters see only a small chance of flash flooding as the weather system, which made landfall in Florida as a hurricane, winds toward New England over the weekend.
dc:creator: Derrick Bryson Taylor and McKenna Oxenden

media:description: Beachfront homes were devastated when Nicole hit Daytona Beach, Fla., on Thursday as a Category 1 hurricane. An hour later, it was downgraded to a tropical storm.
